body:
# Chat Completions

The Chat Completions API generates text from a conversation of messages. Each message has a `role` (system, user, assistant, or tool) and `content`. The model responds with an assistant message.

## Basic Usage

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI(); // reads OPENAI_API_KEY from env

const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [
    { role: "system", content: "You are a helpful assistant." },
    { role: "user", content: "Explain quantum computing in one paragraph." },
  ],
});

console.log(completion.choices[0].message.content);
```

## Streaming

Stream responses token-by-token using Server-Sent Events:

```javascript
const stream = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Write a poem about code." }],
  stream: true,
});

for await (const chunk of stream) {
  const content = chunk.choices[0]?.delta?.content || "";
  process.stdout.write(content);
}
```

## System Prompts

The system message sets the model's behavior, personality, and constraints:

```javascript
messages: [
  {
    role: "system",
    content: "You are a senior software engineer. Respond with concise, production-ready code. Always include error handling."
  },
  { role: "user", content: "Write a function to parse CSV files." },
]
```

## Structured Output

Constrain the model to output valid JSON matching a schema:

```javascript
const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Extract the name and age from: John is 30 years old." }],
  response_format: {
    type: "json_schema",
    json_schema: {
      name: "person",
      schema: {
        type: "object",
        properties: {
          name: { type: "string" },
          age: { type: "integer" },
        },
        required: ["name", "age"],
      },
    },
  },
});
```

## Vision

GPT-4o accepts image inputs alongside text:

```javascript
const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [
    {
      role: "user",
      content: [
        { type: "text", text: "What is in this image?" },
        { type: "image_url", image_url: { url: "https://example.com/photo.jpg" } },
      ],
    },
  ],
});
```

## Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `model` | string | Model ID (e.g. `gpt-4o`, `gpt-4o-mini`, `o1`) |
| `messages` | array | Conversation messages with role and content |
| `temperature` | number | Sampling temperature 0-2 (default 1). Lower = more deterministic |
| `max_tokens` | integer | Maximum tokens to generate |
| `stream` | boolean | Enable streaming responses |
| `tools` | array | Tool definitions for function calling (see [[openai/function-calling]]) |
| `response_format` | object | Constrain output format (json_object or json_schema) |

See [[openai/models]] for model selection guidance and [[openai/function-calling]] for tool integration.
